summary: CRASH - Display Stress 4-hour WDDM Profile Filter id :3209 Expires : 12/30/2016 (REG:116101814815386)
Description: AutoTriage: CRASH - Display Stress 4-hour WDDM Profile - ""System was found to have rebooted unexpectedly"" Auto-Triage detail Filter id :  3209  Expires :  12/30/2016  Type :  AutoTriage  Issue description :  The ""CRASH - Display Stress 4-hour"" test may fail with the logged error ""System was found to have rebooted unexpectedly..."". The error may also be preceeded by a message that no dump file was found. This message indicates the test finished earlier than expected, but no crashdump was found.    Resolution description :  If the machine did not actually crash or stop responding, and was not rebooted, the error may be logged incorrectly. 1) Please ensure the Client system time is in sync (same time zone and time) with the HCK Controller, Other items to check: 2) Client machine should be running English version of OS, with English (US) regional settings, and 3) Set the Client machine Advanced System Settings to create a Kernel Memory or Full dump file, and not ""Automatic"".  Features :  NA Operating system : Windows 10 / 7 64bit   Impact: CRASH - Display Stress 4-hour WDDM Profile (64bit) test will fail & Impact log generation (Windows 7 64 bit) Build:16.50-161004a-307627E-ATI   The errata should be extended or fixed

Instead the repodata is present in the following location.: http://atlaptyum.amd.com/rhel/6/mainline/amdgpu-pro/x86_64/ .But in amdgpu-pro.repo file the baseurl is pointing to 6.9/mainline where there is no mainline folder. If this happens, make sure a debugger gets connected, and the system is booted /DEBUG.  This will let us see why this breakpoint is happening. summary: BugCheck C4 observed during driver uninstallation with verifier enabled over Win7-32 OS
Description: Discription: BugCheck C4 observed during driver uninstallation with verifier enabled over Win7-32 OS Platform Information:- OS Name                  Microsoft Windows 7 Enterprise (32bit) OS Build                 7601 Chipset                  f2a85xm-d3h CPU                      AMD A10-5800K APU with Radeon(tm) HD Graphics CPU Speed               3800 MHz Primary ASIC Name CI KICKER Build : \\hydincbt03\build\1806121513\image\18.30\18.30_BR230356 Steps to reproduce:- Boot into the required setup Install the driver from above path Once Installed �enable driver verifier� �atikmdag.sys� �atikmpg.sys� Reboot the system once enabled driver verifier. Clean Uninstall driver & while uninstalling reported issue will encounter. Expected Result:- Clean Uninstallation should be successful when driver verifier is enabled. Actual Result:- Clean uninstallation failed with Unexpected reboot when driver verifier is enabled. Observation:- Issue observed only on Win7x32 bit configurations. Issue not observed without driver verifier enabled on failed build. Regression data:- Failed build� 1806121513 (CL# 1567297) Passed build�1806111803(CL# 1566821) Complete Dump Analysis: http://tp-sw-appserver.amd.com/DumpPlus2/Dump/View/35207 Dump Analysis:-   ************************************************** *                                                             * *                Bugcheck Analysis                * *                                                              * *************************************************** Use !analyze -v to get detailed debugging information. BugCheck C4, {62, 8f6aa92c, 8f6a9db0, 1} DRIVER_VERIFIER_DETECTED_VIOLATION (c4) A device driver attempting to corrupt the system has been caught.  This is because the driver was specified in the registry as being suspect (by the administrator) and the kernel has enabled substantial checking of this driver. If the driver attempts to corrupt the system, bugchecks 0xC4, 0xC1 and 0xA will be among the most commonly seen crashes. Arguments: Arg1: 00000062, A driver has forgotten to free its pool allocations prior to unloading. Arg2: 8f6aa92c, name of the driver having the issue. Arg3: 8f6a9db0, verifier internal structure with driver information. Arg4: 00000001, total # of (paged+nonpaged) allocations that weren't freed.                 Type !verifier 3 drivername.sys for info on the allocations                 that were leaked that caused the bug check.

summary: [c] [IV][Cert][Win8.1 64] WDDM Toaster - Invalid Param Fourth Group is failing
Description: [Detailed_Description]: Problem Description ------------------------------- WDDM Toaster - Invalid Param Fourth Group test is failing in Win8.1 64 bit on CI/SI/EG/NI System Configuration: ---------------------------------- OS Win8.1 64 bit HCK Version QFE11 CPU AMD Phenom(tm) II X6 1100T Processor ASIC CI MARS ASIC ID 6601 Chipset m5a99x-evo Driver \\hydincbt03\build\1412311900\image\15.20\15.20_BR021649 Steps for repro: ------------------------ 1. Install Windows Blue 64 Bit OS. 2. Install Display Driver specified above 3. Run the tests specified below with HCK 2.1 studio. Job ID Job Name Pass Fail 427 WDDM Bit Flip - Invalid Param Fifth Group 1 1 Expected result: ------------------------- Tests should pass without any issues. Actual Result: ---------------------- Test is failing. Note: ---------- Test passed on VI. [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: EPR #412026 - [IV][Cert][Win8.1 64] WDDM Toaster - Invalid Param Fourth Group is failing [Description] Emulating displays over MST hub and hotplugging entire hub will cuase BSOD at a relatively high frequency (1/5). [Root Cause] During interrupt handling of MST emulation, there were re-entrancy issues where MsgAuxClient interrupts were somehow ending up executing DAL internal code. [Resolution] Redirect internal DAL code execution into interrupt handler for MST Emulation rather than in MstMgrWithEmulation::ProcessDiscoveryFinished where it was originally. Expected: ======== Everything should launch withourt any issues Actual: ====== 1) APP CRASH with a faulty module pointing to ""atigktxx.dll"" while launching (Refer the attachments) Note: ------- >> No issue when we launch or run the app on iGPU.(Intel chipset) Regression: ========= >> FAIL with 15.20Alpha5 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> FAIL with 15.20Alpha4 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> FAIL with 15.20Alpha3 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> PASS with 15.20Alpha2 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> PASS with 15.20Alpha1 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> PASS with 15.10Alpha20 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: - EPR is hybridgraphics only, not PX related. - rootcause: ulFamily is probably not intended to be used as vendor id despite what's said in the comment. we can't use this field to populate our devlist's vendor id field - since we know we are filling info for our hybrid discrete GPU, we'll just fill in the vendor id field instead. - fix CL#1119520 promoted to mainline 2/24/2015.

summary: [IV][Android][Lollipop][Mainline]: Vidtry app is not able to play the video after background to foreground application switch
Description: [Detailed_Description]: System : ======= ASIC : CZ 9874 (A1) BIOS : TGA1002C OS : Lolipop Memory :4 GB Android build : \\amd.com\swblds\CONSTRUCTICON2\raw\186713\android\ll.prototype (OSDB#186713) Steps to Reproduce : =================== On Android client: 1. Install android build. ( Connect HDMI Display) 2. Boot to new image. 3. Locate Vidtry icon and click on it 4. Type the full pathname of the video file (any MPEG4 file) in the textbox (Example /sdcard/Download/MPEG4_30FPS.mp4) and click Go! 5. After 10 seconds, click HOME button 7. Click multitask button and switch to Vidtry application again Expected : Video plays without corruption, skipping, tearing, or hanging. Actual: When we switch to Background by clicking the HOME button -> Audio is audible which is not happening with Gallery application When we switch to Foreground by clicking the multitask button -> Video is not seen but audio is audible Observation with Gallery application: When Gallery application is put in background ( by clicking HOME button ) -> Audio is not audible which is expected When Gallery application is put to foreground ( by clicking multitask button ) -> Video & Audio plays fine Regression: This test scenario was not tested earlier from the inception. Hence there is no regression point. [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: Explanation: Vidtry doesn't pause video playback when home button is pressed during playback. The application disconnect the video surface but audio continue to play in the background. When vidtry resume it can't get back lost surface but a new video playback can be restarted by pressing ""go"" button again. The behavior is same with vidtry on standard Nexus phone and issue found to be with application not supporing pause when home button is pressed. Recommentation: Pause and resume using home button is not recommended for vidtry application. The usecase if exist to be tested only with Gallery and not with vidtry anymore.

After driver installation install SDK by test-set : IV_AutoN_OCL_L1 --> Install_AMD_APP_StreamSDK_3.0_Win32_64 4. After installtion of SDK run the following samples BoxFilterGL.exe and GaussianNoiseGL.exe by command "" sample -e --device gpu 5. On multiple re-runs the samples crash. Out of 5 multiple runs 3 times the issue is observed. The following samples fail Regression: ========= 15.30-150726n-021649E-ATI ---Fail 15.30-150716n-021649E-ATI ---Fail 15.30-150715-021649E-ATI --- Build failure 15.30-150714-021649E-ATI --- Pass logs attached at : \\hydinlogs01\logs$\HY-IN-IVT5\HY-IN-IVT5-42\IV_Run_AMD_APP_OpenCL_Samples_GPU_SDK_3.x_2.x_Win_2015-07-27-11#26#22#154 Observations: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Observing the same failure on the following configuration: PI FIJI PRO ( 7300; winblu-64 ) Triaging: ============ Replaced atikmdag.sys file from fail driver ( 15.30-150716n-021649E-ATI ) to pass driver ( 15.30-150714-021649E-ATI ) --> Fail [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: Problem: TDR happens after triggers GFX MCBP Root cause: RB META data entry was filled with NOPs because KMD failed detect preemptible draw IB. Solution: When detecting a preemptible IB, make sure it is not CE Preamble IB because CE Preamble IB is not preemptible. Same root cause as EPR #424058, KMD CL#1174872 fixes the issue.

summary: [IV_Perf][Win10-64bit] Blank screen observed during running PCmark8 (Creative3.0) subtest on CZ Board
Description: [Detailed_Description]: [IV_Perf][Win10-64bit] Blank screen observed during running PCmark8 (Creative3.0) subtest on CZ Board =========================================================================================================== Configuration ------------------ CPU: AMD FX 8800PRadeon R7, 12 compute cores4C+8G 2.10GHz OS : Win10-64bit , 10240 RTM image Chipset gardenia ASIC : FUSION CARIZO Device ID : 9874 BIOS VERSION:WGA5819N RAM: 6 GB Display: HDMI Monitor Connected Build Location : \\hydincbt03\build\1508231900\image\15.30\15.30_BR021649 Steps to reproduce: ------------------------------- - Set up the above configuration - Install the above said mainline nightly driver - Install PCmark8 thru TACC or manually Test set: NPI_Install_PCMark_8 [Ver:304] - Launch PCmark8 bench and go to Developer->Creative3.0->Select all the subtests - wait for 10-20 minutes to observed the Blank screen Expected: ---------- PCmark8->Creative3.0 should run properly with appropriate results Actual: --------- Blank screen is observed during PCmark8->creative3.0 running Regression ------------ 15.30-150823n-021649E-ATI - FAIL 15.30-150728n-021649E-ATI - PASS NOTE ===== During PCmark8->Creative3.0 running when it comes to (Video group chatv2) the blank screen is observed. [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: Please verify that the latest SystemInfo file from PCMark is installed. Latest version is: Version 4.40 | August 20, 2015 http://www.futuremark.com/support/systeminfo Change 1188018 by jlu@stg-kmd-jameslu-64 on 2015/09/04 09:06:45 EPR #425606 - [IV_Perf][Win10-64bit] Blank screen observed during running PCmark8 (Creative3.0) subtest on CZ Board [Problem/Feature Description] Blank screen observed during running PCmark8 (Creative3.0) subtest on CZ Board [Solution Description] There is VM page fault because the private VA PD is not updated in process' Page Directory due to Window 10 bug (VSO 4448217). Before Microsoft fixes it in the Windows 10 future release, KMD driver needs to workaround it. 1. Add a flag ""m_IsPrivateVaPdUpdated"" in KdProcess to track the PrivateVaPD update information. 2. During process' PD update, if ""InitialUpdate"" for PD update is set, KMD will update PrivateVa PDE and set ""m_IsPrivateVaPdUpdated"" in KdProcess. If ""InitialUpdate"" is not set for PD update, KMD driver should check ""m_IsPrivateVaPdUpdated"" in KdProcess to decide if the PrivateVa PDE should be updated. [Code Review] http://codereview/go?page=ReviewDisplay&reviewid=54360 Affected files ... //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/Doc/Workarounds/KMD Workarounds.xls#69 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/inc/Workaround_types.hpp#84 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/kdx/src/PagingContext.cpp#146 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/kdx/src/Process.cpp#24 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/kdx/src/Process.hpp#12 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/kdx/src/VmPageTable.hpp#37 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/src/WorkaroundManager.cpp#121 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/src/WorkaroundManager.hpp#60 edit

summary: Wrong denotation of display orientation observed on 4K sharp monitor.
Description: Issue : Wrong denotation of display orientation observed on 4K sharp monitor. System Details: Graphics Chipset - AMD Radeon R9 200 Series (Hawaii Gemini) Memory Size - 4096 MB Memory Type - GDDR5 Core Clock - 1000 MHz Windows Version - Windows 10 (64 bit) System Memory - 10 GB CPU Type - AMD FX(tm)-8150 Eight-Core Processor Driver Packaging Version - 16.20-160302a-300002E-ATI Display Monitor: 4K Sharp display Use a HDMI connection only for display monitor   Steps to Repro: 1) Set up the above configuration. 2) Install the system with mentioned driver packaging version 3) Restart the system when asked after the installation. 4) Go to display properties by right click on desktop 5) Try checking the orientation of the display   Actual Result: Wrong denotation of display orientation observed i.e. when the display is kept in Landscape mode it is showing Potrait and the vice versa. Also is the case for flipped modes.   Expected result landscape to be shown when the display is in landscape mode. Same is the case for all the modes.   Regression info: 1) Issue observed with specifically 4K Sharp monitor only (in both MST & SST Streaming) 2) Issue observed on  > 16.20 ( Alpha 5) + Fiji PRO + Win 7 64 bit --> PASS  > 16.20 ( Alpha 5) + Hawaii Gemini + Win 10 64 bit --> FAIL  > 16.20 ( Alpha 3) + Hawaii Gemini + Win 10 64 bit --> FAIL  > 15.30 ( Beta 9) + Hawaii Gemini + Win 10 64 bit --> FAIL 3) Issue is specific to 4K Sharp monitor only. 4) Issue not observed on other Samsung or ASUS 4K display monitors. 5) Issue observed with only HDMI connection and not observed on DP port. Note: Hawaii Gemini (VESUVIUS) doesn't have HDMI port. Use a mini DP to HDMI dongle to make the set up.
